    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Past Its Time?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Martin Tessler letter on Anthony Tommasini's August 25 article holds New York Times should stop using phrase classical composer</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Speaking as a future ''dead white male'' (like the classical composers Anthony Tommasini alludes to), isn't it time for The New York Times to exorcise this phrase, as it has done with other words that are no longer politically correct?</p>
        <p>MARTIN TESSLER  Manhattan</p>
      </block>
